52 * jerror.h
53 *
54 * Copyright (C) 1994-1997, Thomas G. Lane.
55 * This file is part of the Independent JPEG Group's software.
56 * For conditions of distribution and use, see the accompanying README file.
57 *
58 * This file defines the error and message codes for the JPEG library.
59 * Edit this file to add new codes, or to translate the message strings to
60 * some other language.
61 * A set of error-reporting macros are defined too. Some applications using
62 * the JPEG library may wish to include this file to get the error codes
63 * and/or the macros.
64 */
65
66/*
67 * To define the enum list of message codes, include this file without
68 * defining macro JMESSAGE. To create a message string table, include it
69 * again with a suitable JMESSAGE definition (see jerror.c for an example).
70 */

75#else
76/* Repeated inclusions of this file are no-ops unless JMESSAGE is defined */
77#define JMESSAGE(code,string)
78#endif /* JERROR_H */
79#endif /* JMESSAGE */

250/* Macros to simplify using the error and trace message stuff */
251/* The first parameter is either type of cinfo pointer */
252
253/* Fatal errors (print message and exit) */
254#define ERREXIT(cinfo,code) \
255 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
256 (*(cinfo)->err->error_exit) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo)))
257#define ERREXIT1(cinfo,code,p1) \
258 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
259 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[0] = (p1), \
260 (*(cinfo)->err->error_exit) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo)))
261#define ERREXIT2(cinfo,code,p1,p2) \
262 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
263 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[0] = (p1), \
264 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[1] = (p2), \
265 (*(cinfo)->err->error_exit) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo)))
266#define ERREXIT3(cinfo,code,p1,p2,p3) \
267 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
268 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[0] = (p1), \
269 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[1] = (p2), \
270 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[2] = (p3), \
271 (*(cinfo)->err->error_exit) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo)))
272#define ERREXIT4(cinfo,code,p1,p2,p3,p4) \
273 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
274 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[0] = (p1), \
275 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[1] = (p2), \
276 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[2] = (p3), \
277 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[3] = (p4), \
278 (*(cinfo)->err->error_exit) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo)))
279#define ERREXITS(cinfo,code,str) \
280 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
281 strncpy((cinfo)->err->msg_parm.s, (str), JMSG_STR_PARM_MAX), \
282 (*(cinfo)->err->error_exit) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo)))
283
284#define MAKESTMT(stuff) do { stuff } while (0)
285
286/* Nonfatal errors (we can keep going, but the data is probably corrupt) */
287#define WARNMS(cinfo,code) \
288 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
289 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), -1))
290#define WARNMS1(cinfo,code,p1) \
291 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
292 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[0] = (p1), \
293 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), -1))
294#define WARNMS2(cinfo,code,p1,p2) \
295 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
296 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[0] = (p1), \
297 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[1] = (p2), \
298 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), -1))
299
300/* Informational/debugging messages */
301#define TRACEMS(cinfo,lvl,code) \
302 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
303 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), (lvl)))
304#define TRACEMS1(cinfo,lvl,code,p1) \
305 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
306 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[0] = (p1), \
307 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), (lvl)))
308#define TRACEMS2(cinfo,lvl,code,p1,p2) \
309 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
310 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[0] = (p1), \
311 (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i[1] = (p2), \
312 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), (lvl)))
313#define TRACEMS3(cinfo,lvl,code,p1,p2,p3) \
314 MAKESTMT(int * _mp = (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i; \
315 _mp[0] = (p1); _mp[1] = (p2); _mp[2] = (p3); \
316 (cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code); \
317 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), (lvl)); )
318#define TRACEMS4(cinfo,lvl,code,p1,p2,p3,p4) \
319 MAKESTMT(int * _mp = (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i; \
320 _mp[0] = (p1); _mp[1] = (p2); _mp[2] = (p3); _mp[3] = (p4); \
321 (cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code); \
322 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), (lvl)); )
323#define TRACEMS5(cinfo,lvl,code,p1,p2,p3,p4,p5) \
324 MAKESTMT(int * _mp = (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i; \
325 _mp[0] = (p1); _mp[1] = (p2); _mp[2] = (p3); _mp[3] = (p4); \
326 _mp[4] = (p5); \
327 (cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code); \
328 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), (lvl)); )
329#define TRACEMS8(cinfo,lvl,code,p1,p2,p3,p4,p5,p6,p7,p8) \
330 MAKESTMT(int * _mp = (cinfo)->err->msg_parm.i; \
331 _mp[0] = (p1); _mp[1] = (p2); _mp[2] = (p3); _mp[3] = (p4); \
332 _mp[4] = (p5); _mp[5] = (p6); _mp[6] = (p7); _mp[7] = (p8); \
333 (cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code); \
334 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), (lvl)); )
335#define TRACEMSS(cinfo,lvl,code,str) \
336 ((cinfo)->err->msg_code = (code), \
337 strncpy((cinfo)->err->msg_parm.s, (str), JMSG_STR_PARM_MAX), \
338 (*(cinfo)->err->cemit_message) ((j_common_ptr) (cinfo), (lvl)))
339
340#endif /* JERROR_H */
